of survival is 12%.

563
00:55:47,960 --> 00:55:51,080
12%?! Can't you come up with better odds?

564
00:55:51,160 --> 00:55:54,680
- Nope.
- Bullshit, Kay-Em! That's bullshit!

565
00:55:54,760 --> 00:55:58,160
Preparation for launch may be
a relatively simple procedure,

566
00:55:58,200 --> 00:56:00,200
but getting there alive...

567
00:56:00,280 --> 00:56:01,800
It is a problem.

568
00:56:01,880 --> 00:56:03,440
Are you telling me
there's absolutely

569
00:56:03,480 --> 00:56:05,880
no chance for us
to better our odds?!

570
00:56:13,080 --> 00:56:14,960
Statistical probability
of survival

571
00:56:15,000 --> 00:56:18,800
just went up to 53%.

572
00:56:18,840 --> 00:56:20,840
You want to go for 100?

573
00:56:51,080 --> 00:56:52,720
He's here.

574
00:56:52,760 --> 00:56:54,960
Quiet.

575
00:56:55,000 --> 00:56:57,240
But if he's in here,
he's going to kill us.

576
00:56:57,280 --> 00:56:58,600
Be quiet.

577
00:56:58,680 --> 00:57:01,840
One more sound and I'll
snap your neck myself.

578
00:57:01,880 --> 00:57:05,920
- Got it?
- She's good with people.

579
00:57:07,960 --> 00:57:09,680
- Did you see that?
- What?

580
00:57:09,720 --> 00:57:11,920
I think there's someone
still alive over there.

581
00:57:14,360 --> 00:57:16,400
We don't have time
for this.

582
00:57:21,880 --> 00:57:23,200
Which way
is the shuttle bay?

583
00:57:23,280 --> 00:57:24,840
Straight through.

584
00:57:24,920 --> 00:57:27,720
Go. I'll meet you there.

585
00:57:30,920 --> 00:57:33,800
Just don't wreck
my pants.

586
00:58:04,040 --> 00:58:06,960
Come on, girl.
We're going home.

587
00:58:23,680 --> 00:58:25,680
<i>Crutch:
Oh, Lou.</i>

588
00:58:27,600 --> 00:58:29,880
<i>Waylander:
Jesus, that's twisted.</i>

589
00:58:32,720 --> 00:58:35,720
Of course,
I've seen worse.

590
00:58:38,200 --> 00:58:40,200
Okay, let's get
to work.

591
00:58:56,320 --> 00:58:58,200
Brodski?

592
00:59:06,360 --> 00:59:08,200
Okay.

593
00:59:08,280 --> 00:59:10,480
We're going to get you
out of here.

594
00:59:10,520 --> 00:59:12,680
- No.
- Oh, God.

595
00:59:14,240 --> 00:59:17,360
I'm going to go get help
and I'll be back.

596
00:59:26,680 --> 00:59:28,640
Give me your vest.

597
00:59:31,840 --> 00:59:33,280
Oh, bastard.

598
00:59:33,360 --> 00:59:36,200
Hey... be lucky
you weren't alive

599
00:59:36,280 --> 00:59:38,360
during the Microsoft
conflict.

600
00:59:38,440 --> 00:59:41,160
We were beating each other
with our own severed limbs.

601
00:59:41,240 --> 00:59:42,840
That's nice.

602
00:59:42,880 --> 00:59:44,760
Okay.

603
00:59:44,840 --> 00:59:46,840
Let's get us home.

604
00:59:46,920 --> 00:59:49,280
- Kinsa, are you there?
- Yes, ma'am.

605
00:59:49,360 --> 00:59:52,240
- Crutch? - Prepare for fuel transfer.

606
00:59:52,280 --> 00:59:55,480
- Cell six and seven bypass.
- Hydraulic lifters.

607
00:59:57,520 --> 00:59:59,480
Pressurized and damped.

608
00:59:59,560 --> 01:00:02,920
- It's Brodski. He's alive. - No shit?

609
01:00:03,000 --> 01:00:05,480
Yeah. I can't move him.
Are way and crutch back?

610
01:00:05,560 --> 01:00:08,120
- No, they're still on the bridge.
- I need help.

611
01:00:08,160 --> 01:00:10,480
Hey, guys,
Brodski's still alive.

612
01:00:10,520 --> 01:00:12,640
<i>But rowan can't move him
by herself.</i>

613
01:00:12,720 --> 01:00:14,680
Go, go, go. I can handle it from here.

614
01:00:14,720 --> 01:00:17,080
Tell them I'm on my way.
Watch your back.

615
01:00:18,440 --> 01:00:20,800
Crutch, how we doing
for time?

616
01:00:20,880 --> 01:00:23,800
With a giant shitload
of good luck,

617
01:00:23,840 --> 01:00:26,560
we might be ready to go.

618
01:00:26,640 --> 01:00:28,400
Good.

619
01:00:31,720 --> 01:00:34,360
Rowan. Hey.
Where's Brodski?

620
01:00:34,400 --> 01:00:37,200
I-- he was here.
I don't get it.

621
01:00:37,240 --> 01:00:41,400
And I am going home.

622
01:00:43,200 --> 01:00:45,400
Lowe!
[Laughs]

623
01:00:45,480 --> 01:00:48,720
Oh, shit!
I got company here, people!

624
01:00:48,760 --> 01:00:51,120
<i>[Crutch screams]</i>

625
01:00:54,120 --> 01:00:55,840
Let's go.

626
01:01:03,760 --> 01:01:07,480
Kinsa, open the door.
Open the damn door!

627
01:01:18,440 --> 01:01:21,440
- Why aren't you on board?
- Kinsa won't open the door.

628
01:01:21,520 --> 01:01:23,240
I think that she's
finally lost it

629
01:01:23,320 --> 01:01:25,640
and this is a really
bad time for this!

630
01:01:25,720 --> 01:01:27,920
Janessa,
give me the comm.

631
01:01:27,960 --> 01:01:30,200
Kinsa, kinsa honey,
it's rowan.

632
01:01:30,280 --> 01:01:31,960
I need you to open
the door.

633
01:01:32,000 --> 01:01:34,040
No.

634
01:01:34,120 --> 01:01:36,000
Kinsa, sweetheart,
it's all over.

635
01:01:36,080 --> 01:01:38,840
We can go home. All you need
to do is open the door for us.

636
01:01:38,920 --> 01:01:41,160
No.

637
01:01:41,240 --> 01:01:43,800
<i>- [Rumbling]
- Come on, guys!</i>

638
01:01:43,840 --> 01:01:46,880
Jesus Christ, kinsa,
open the goddamn door!

639
01:01:51,160 --> 01:01:53,880
Oh no, kinsa, the fuel
lines are still attached!

640
01:01:59,240 --> 01:02:01,080
Kinsa!

641
01:02:19,960 --> 01:02:21,880
Now what?

642
01:02:24,960 --> 01:02:27,480
Now basically we die.

643
01:02:27,560 --> 01:02:29,480
Bullshit!

644
01:02:30,880 --> 01:02:32,280
Okay, new plan.

645
01:02:32,360 --> 01:02:34,360
You hold him
and I'll run.

646
01:02:42,200 --> 01:02:43,640
Hey, slappy.

647
01:02:43,720 --> 01:02:45,560
I got a little
something for you.

648
01:02:53,240 --> 01:02:57,240
- Oh, wow.
- I gave her an upload.

649
01:02:57,320 --> 01:02:59,960
I'm afraid I'm going
to have to hurt you now.

650
01:03:03,120 --> 01:03:04,600
Kay-Em!

651
01:03:12,280 --> 01:03:15,800
That-- that didn't
go so well.

652
01:03:20,680 --> 01:03:22,120
Gotcha!

653
01:03:34,360 --> 01:03:35,400
Hey.

654
01:04:21,560 --> 01:04:22,960
Giddy-up.

655
01:04:32,000 --> 01:04:34,840
I had it under control,
but thanks.

656
01:04:37,080 --> 01:04:38,800
My pleasure.

657
01:05:24,680 --> 01:05:26,520
Yeah.

658
01:05:43,280 --> 01:05:46,160
- You did it.
- Kay-Em!

659
01:05:46,200 --> 01:05:47,880
Who's your mama?

660
01:05:48,760 --> 01:05:50,840
All right!

661
01:05:50,880 --> 01:05:54,040
- How you doing there, Brodski?
- I'm all right.

662
01:05:54,080 --> 01:05:55,960
Come on, let's get you
patched up.

663
01:05:56,040 --> 01:05:57,520
<i>What a mess.</i>

664
01:05:57,560 --> 01:05:59,640
Lab two.

665
01:06:07,960 --> 01:06:11,160
- Tsunaron, is he going to make it?
- Absolutely.

666
01:06:11,240 --> 01:06:12,800
He's at 80% already.

667
01:06:12,880 --> 01:06:14,200
<i>This guy is strong.</i>

668
01:06:14,240 --> 01:06:15,800
<i>[Rumbling]</i>

669
01:06:15,840 --> 01:06:18,680
<i>[Alarm blaring]</i>

670
01:06:18,720 --> 01:06:20,640
What the hell?

671
01:06:25,080 --> 01:06:26,720
Way?

672
01:06:27,560 --> 01:06:29,400
We've got trouble.

673
01:06:29,440 --> 01:06:33,120
The collision must have compromised the hull.
She's bleeding out.

674
01:06:33,200 --> 01:06:37,160
Oh, no.
No, no, no.

675
01:06:37,240 --> 01:06:39,760
<i>Tiamat to grendel.
Do you read? Over.</i>

676
01:06:39,800 --> 01:06:42,200
<i>Tiamat to grendel.
Do you read?</i>

677
01:06:42,280 --> 01:06:44,560
Yes, tiamat, this is grendel.
We read you.

678
01:06:44,600 --> 01:06:46,480
<i>- Can you hear us?
- That's affirmative.</i>

679
01:06:46,520 --> 01:06:48,360
<i>We are reading
your distress beacon.</i>

680
01:06:48,440 --> 01:06:51,640
<i>- Are you in need of assistance?
- That's very affirmative.</i>

681
01:06:51,720 --> 01:06:55,320
How soon can you get here?
Our situation is critical.

682
01:06:55,400 --> 01:06:57,560
<i>We're four parsecs away,
grendel.</i>

683
01:06:57,600 --> 01:07:00,960
<i>Eta, 45 minutes.</i>

684
01:07:01,040 --> 01:07:03,080
We don't have
that much time.

685
01:07:03,160 --> 01:07:05,520
Tiamat, this is grendel.
Our hull is bleeding out.

686
01:07:05,560 --> 01:07:08,240
We're going to have a core
implosion in less than 30 minutes.

687
01:07:08,280 --> 01:07:09,880
<i>Do you copy?</i>

688
01:07:09,920 --> 01:07:11,920
<i>Tiamat:
We copy you, grendel.</i>

689
01:07:11,960 --> 01:07:13,760
<i>Advise how you would
like us to proceed.</i>

690
01:07:13,840 --> 01:07:16,320
We're just going to end up
taking them down with us.

691
01:07:21,160 --> 01:07:23,680
Tiamat,

692
01:07:23,760 --> 01:07:26,480
if you can't get here in 30
minutes, then there's no point.

693
01:07:26,520 --> 01:07:28,920
What, are you high?!
Tiamat, this is grendel.

694
01:07:29,000 --> 01:07:31,080
You just ignore
that last idiot, all right?!

695
01:07:31,160 --> 01:07:33,720
You get your ass
out here, okay?

696
01:07:33,760 --> 01:07:35,440
You come here,
and you save us!

697
01:07:35,480 --> 01:07:37,880
Hey, why can't we just
go over here?

698
01:07:37,960 --> 01:07:40,400
It's no good.
If the pontoon goes,

699
01:07:40,440 --> 01:07:41,880
